# ============================================================================
# MicroManagerr .gitignore
# ============================================================================
# This file tells Git which files and folders to IGNORE (not track).
# Why ignore files? Some files are:
#   - Generated (can be recreated)
#   - Environment-specific (different on each machine)
#   - Sensitive (contain secrets/passwords)
#   - Large (binary files, dependencies)
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
# Python creates these automatically when running code - they speed up imports
# but can be regenerated anytime, so no need to track them
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# C extensions (compiled Python modules)
*.so

# Distribution / packaging
# These are created when you build your package for distribution
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
share/python-wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# PyInstaller
# Usually these files are written by a python script from a template
*.manifest
*.spec

